    public static class ComponentAdapter.Associations

    • Method Detail

      • get

        public static java.lang.Class<? extends ComponentAdapter> get(java.lang.Class<?> objectType)
        Get the associated component adapter class associated with a class. If no component adapter class is associated with the supplied class, then its super classes and interfaces are searched until a component adapter association is found.
        Parameters:
        objectType - The class of the object to find associations for.
        Returns:
        The associated component adapter class, or null if none is found.

      • set

        public static void set(java.lang.Class<?> objectType,
                       java.lang.Class<? extends ComponentAdapter> adapterType)
        Associates a component adapter class with an arbitrary class.
        Parameters:
        objectType - The class to make the association for. If an association already exists for this class, then it is overwritten.
        adapterType - The component adapter class to associate with the supplied class. If this is null, then any existing association of the supplied class is removed.
